In this config, the top bar shows the ram usage, battery life, available updates, etc.
One downside is that users will have to personally change the time config in i3status.conf to their own timezone as the config for the time module is static
All the brightness, volume, play and pause keys actually work.
mod+t opens rofi -show run
mod+d opens rofi -show drun
mod+c opens clipmenu
Everything else works as normal in i3
conky is included as a depend, but none are preset as the bar itself already offers so much information
